formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1) We have relied on the work of an expert who has issued Form 1 and Form 2 for the quarterly RERA Return Submission.
2) It is the responsibility of the promoter to provide the Mobile No. of allottee and we have relied on the information provided.
3) The Certificate has been prepared based on the financial data made available to us for verification and we have relied on the
financial data and bank statements provided to us.
4) The promoter could not executed an agreement to sell for Unit No. A-6 and B-4 as the Allottee could not came for registration on the appointed date and time and has provided the promoter confirmation that they are aware of the non compliance of the RERA Act in this regard and they shall have no objection for non execution of ATS even through promoter had informed them about it.
5) Loan taken by the promoter has been fully repaid and lender has issued No due certificate in the name of the promoter.
6) The project has received BU permission on 18-10-2022. the promoter had estimated interest cost of rs. 7.20 Crore however due to good response in the booking at the early stage of construction, the promoter had completed the project by utilizing the funds from booking and resulted into less payment towards interest cost as compared to expected interest cost for the project.
